\note[enumerate]{
\item Node moves from AR1 to AR2
\item Packets are lost at link to AR1 (packets on link = bandwidth delay product, but 
\begin{itemize}
\item CCN can be connected to AR1 and AR2 simultaneously and still get the returning packets
\item Packets are also cached at AR2
\end{itemize}
\item $\rightarrow$ CCN more efficient on frequent handovers than IP
}

