\item Cost-awareness: Modeling costs of access paths (provider traffic limits, charge per MB, power consumption, etc.)
\item Measuring Interface performance to choose the best interface for each traffic class.
\item Bluetooth: Cannot be combined with other types of access networks in IP (again because of complexity)
\item Selective redundancy: Not flooding, but something more intelligent, taking QoS into account.
\item Devil \& Details: Interface probing, Interest Lifetime retx, Max. strategy state, Constrained optimization
}

\begin{frame}{Interdependence with the Link-Layer}
\vspace{-3mm}
\begin{columns}[T]
\column{0.45\linewidth}
\centering
\includegraphics[width=1.05\linewidth]{images/hourglass_retx.pdf}\\
Retransmissions in IP
\vspace{10cm}
\column{0.55\linewidth}
\begin{block}{IP packet loss $\rightarrow$ ARQ}
\begin{enumerate}
\item Request packet again
\item Report loss to higher layer
\end{enumerate}
\end{block}
\end{columns}
\end{frame}

\note[enumerate]{
\item Link-layer agreed for local retx, because IP protocol is designed as simple as possible.
\item Higher-layer retx take much longer
\item ARQ protocols to deal with packet loss: retransmit packets for a number of times (default of 7 in WiFi) or as long as below certain delay.
\item No retransmissions on the network layer, because IP doesn't support it.
}

\begin{frame}{Interdependence with the Link-Layer}
\vspace{-3mm}
\begin{columns}[T]
\column{0.45\linewidth}
\centering
\includegraphics[width=1.05\linewidth]{images/hourglass_retx_ccn.pdf}\\
Retransmissions in CCN
\vspace{10cm}
\column{0.55\linewidth}
\begin{block}{$\rightarrow$ Local Retx and Redundancy on the CCN Strategy Layer}
\begin{itemize}
\item Tailored to app. requirements
\item Knowledge of multiple paths
\end{itemize}
\end{block}
\vspace{-2mm}
\begin{block}{CCN packet loss}
\begin{enumerate}
\item Request packet again
\item Request on different path
\item Request on multiple paths
\item Report loss to higher layer
\end{enumerate}
\end{block}
\end{columns}
\end{frame}

\note[enumerate]{
\item CCN layer is much more sophisticated than IP $\rightarrow$ Also hop-to-hop: Can be used for local retx!
\item Tailored to application requirements: More local retx for delay-sensitive traffic (VoIP) than for delay-tolerant traffic (file downloads).
\item Knowledge of multiple paths: Introduces two more options. Especially beneficial in real-time communications.
}

